                <div style="clear:both;"></div></aside>
            <!-- Share buttons by mashshare.net - Version: 3.8.1--></div><footer class="entry-footer"><p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-categories">Categories: <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/category/web-pros" rel="category tag">Web Pros</a>, <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/category/website-security" rel="category tag">Website Security</a></span></p></footer></article><section class="author-box"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f7105dd5dc850e545047cfa4477d2343?s=115&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f7105dd5dc850e545047cfa4477d2343?s=230&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-115 photo' height='115' width='115' loading='lazy'/><h4 class="author-box-title">About <span itemprop="name">David Dede</span></h4><div class="author-box-content" itemprop="description"><p>David is a Security Researcher at Sucuri. He spends most of his time dissecting vulnerabilities and security issues. You won't find him on Twitter because he is paranoid about privacy.</p>
